The paper deals with the downlink of a cloud RAN architecture and focuses on interference management. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category. The paper also discusses transmit precoding schemes and evaluates their performance, which could place it in the Information Theory (cs.IT) category. The use of clustering algorithms and the discussion of cost implications suggest that the paper could also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category. The evaluation of performance using simulations suggests that the paper could belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) category. Finally, the discussion of piloting overhead and its impact on system sum-rate suggests that the paper could belong to the Architecture (cs.AR) category.
